ds to RANK ligand to stimulate osteoblast activity","Blocks parathyroid hormone secretion","Binds to RANK ligand to inhibit osteoclast activity","Inhibits calcium absorption in the intestine","Increases vitamin D production in the kidneys"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDenosumab works by \u003Cstrong\u003Ebinding to RANK ligand\u003C/strong\u003E, preventing its interaction with the RANK receptor on osteoclast precursor cells. This \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibits osteoclast formation, differentiation, and activity, \u003C/strong\u003Eleading to decreased bone resorption and increased bone density.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBinds to RANK ligand to stimulates osteoblast activity\u003C/strong\u003E: while denosumab may indirectly allow more bone formation through reduced osteoclast activity, it does not directly stimulate osteoblasts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks parathyroid hormone secretion\u003C/strong\u003E: denosumab has no direct effect on parathyroid hormone production or release.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits calcium absorption in the intestine\u003C/strong\u003E: denosumab does not influence intestinal calcium absorption in any way.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases vitamin D production in the kidneys\u003C/strong\u003E: denosumab does not affect vitamin D metabolism or production.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBy preventing osteoclast-mediated bone resorption, denosumab helps increase bone density in conditions characterised by excessive bone loss.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Denosumab is a monoclonal antibody that inhibits RANK ligand, thereby preventing osteoclast formation and activation.","By reducing osteoclast activity, denosumab decreases bone resorption and increases bone mineral density.","Denosumab is used to treat osteoporosis and prevent skeletal-related events in bone metastases."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62316"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17026"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62316","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62316"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T13:25:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T13:25:55+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9716"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76815"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Rememb